pullRequest.body:
* Remove manual translations that are now guessed correctly
* Fix some names that were incorrectly guessed by humans (and in one case fix the multiplicative name). Add deprecations for all name changes.
* Remove a couple manually additivized lemmas.


---

Is this the right way to deprecate?

nodes.body: This will conflict with #10832. If one is merged, the other PR should merge master.

I can't look carefully at the translations, but the deprecations look correct to me.  The only difference with what I've seen is that the date appeared at the end, but I do not think that there is a style requirement for that.
Yes, I only found it myself by investigating why `to_additive` did *not* warn me about the superfluous name.

Thanks!  I like the advance of automation!

Good catch: this is a very subtle name translation!

(Same goes for the one below!)

Could you uniformize the doc-strings to
* either `Submonoid` (the multiplicative one)
* or "additive submonoid" (the additive one)?

I have a slight preference for using the Lean names, but definitely prefer the symmetry.
